HINDI LIVINUS The Adamawa State Police Command on Saturday confirmed the arrest of two suspects who allegedly defrauded a bank manager of the sum of $200,000 (about N70m). Confirming the arrest in Yola, the spokesman for the command, DSP Suleiman Yahaya, said the suspects, Oluba Falaye, and Abidakun Gbenga, were arrested while two other suspects were still at large. He said, “The command received report from one Olurunfemi Michael, a manager at Access Bank Plc,Yola branch, that on December 11, 2019, some men approached him and defrauded him of $200,000,00 which if converted into naira will be N70,000,000. “Investigation led to the arrest of Oluba Falaye and Abidakun Gbenga, residents of Lagos and Ado-Ekiti (Ekiti State).” Yahaya said $30,400, one Lexus and Toyota Camry cars valued at N14m were recovered from the suspects. “The command is calling on members of the public to be careful while dealing with the people they don’t know and to report to police any suspicious movement around them,” he added. Copyright PUNCH.
